 {"id":"asupersync-3kv3e.4","title":"[audit][stream] Latch Map/Inspect exhaustion to avoid repolling upstream after Ready(None)","description":"src/stream/map.rs and src/stream/inspect.rs return Poll::Ready(None) directly without latching exhaustion, so later polls can repoll exhausted upstream streams. Match the repo's current exhausted-state style (for example enumerate/filter/skip/zip), zero size_hint after exhaustion, add focused regression tests that prove exhausted upstreams are not repolled, and validate with rch-offloaded fmt/check/clippy/test commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SapphireFinch","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-12T21:46:22.009824837Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-12T21:46:22.009824837Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream","terminal-state"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3kv3e.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3kv3e","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-12T21:46:22.009824837Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
